        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-15T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-15T01:00:00-05:00" n="1355" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1355">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">119.2/6—1549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-15T14:00:00+08:00">June 15, 1949—2 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 15—8:04 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1289. Reference Peiping telegram 990 to Department June 11. Embassy would
                    appreciate résumé origin China network, agreements with Nationalist Government,
                    et cetera which Department feels would be valuable in any negotiations with
                    Communists for retention of network.</p>
                <p>Sent Department; repeated Shanghai 700, AmEmb Canton 538.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
